abstract: The authorities are making progress in restricting a website as a medium for sex trafficking.
snippet: The authorities are making progress in restricting a website as a medium for sex trafficking.
lead_paragraph: As a 16-year-old high school sophomore living in Boston, Asia Graves was sold on the internet “like a pizza,” she recalls, handed over to be raped by strange men every day.

abstract: The retired general drew bipartisan support after offering views on immigration and border security differing from those expressed by the president-elect.
snippet: The retired general drew bipartisan support after offering views on immigration and border security differing from those expressed by the president-elect.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Gen. John F. Kelly, President-elect Donald J. Trump’s choice to lead the Department of Homeland Security, easily maneuvered through his confirmation hearing before the Senate Homeland Security Committee on Tuesday, drawing bipartisan support for what is likely be a smooth approval process by the full Senate.

abstract: Though it’s premature to pick a front-runner for the next presidential race, there is reason to speculate about a possible bid by the governor of New York.

lead_paragraph: ALBANY — It had all the trappings of a presidential campaign rollout: the cheering crowd, the flag-draped stage, an appearance and a hearty endorsement from Senator Bernie Sanders of Vermont.

abstract: The state’s Democratic-led Legislature decided to retain Mr. Holder to represent it in any legal fights against the new Republican White House.
snippet: The state’s Democratic-led Legislature decided to retain Mr. Holder to represent it in any legal fights against the new Republican White House.
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — Girding for four years of potential battles with President-elect Donald J. Trump, Democratic leaders of the California Legislature announced Wednesday that they had hired Eric H. Holder Jr., who was attorney general under President Obama, to represent them in any legal fights against the new Republican White House.

headline_main: California Today: Cast Your Vote for Californian of the Year

abstract: A look at what 2014 and 2016 were trying to tell Democrats, such as whether they should be thinking more about class and less about identity politics.
snippet: A look at what 2014 and 2016 were trying to tell Democrats, such as whether they should be thinking more about class and less about identity politics.
lead_paragraph: Nate Cohn, The Upshot’s elections analyst, and Toni Monkovic, an Upshot editor, peeked ahead to 2020 and back at the recent election, posting a lightly edited transcript of their written exchange.

abstract: The announcement brings the threat of a federal lawsuit into a controversy in a California county where some murder convictions have already been overturned.
snippet: The announcement brings the threat of a federal lawsuit into a controversy in a California county where some murder convictions have already been overturned.
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — The Department of Justice opened a civil rights investigation on Thursday into whether the Orange County district attorney’s office improperly used jailhouse informants and withheld evidence.
